evidence.phenotypeFreeText:
omega shaped epiglottis with bilateral arytenoid edema and hooding,  
reddening and swelling of skin of the extremities when in a warm environment or febrile; 
MRI showed revealed a persistent abnormal diffusion signal of the dorsal brainstem, areas of periventricular hypointensity on T1-weghted imaging, and patchy white matter hyperintensities on T2-weighted imaging.
